I love an active political debate, so allow me to introduce you to the ‘ACA’.⠀
⠀
The ACA would be the largest country on Earth, and its land mass would stretch from the North Pole to the sub-tropical seas. The ACA’s GDP (annual economic output, measured by purchasing power parity) would overtake China to become the largest in the world, and its rich natural resources would encourage a more environmentally sustainable existence for its citizens. ACA citizens would lean slightly liberal (left), but still more conservative than the average citizen of other first world nations. The ACA’s elected governments would typically switch between conservative and liberal majorities every 8-10 years.⠀
⠀
1... 2... 3... DISCUSS.

It’s OFFICIAL.  Canada became the 2nd country in the world (1st among G7 nations) to legalize #marijuana on October 17! Be sure to check out @canborder’s entertaining + informative public service announcements 😳😆🤣⠀
⠀
WHAT TO KNOW?⠀
⠀
✔️ YES, consumption of marijuana / cannabis for medicinal, personal or recreational use is LEGAL, WITHIN Canada.⠀
⠀
✘ NO, it is NOT legal to carry, transport, or ship marijuana / cannabis across the border - but if you find yourself crossing with marijuana / cannabis in your possession, DECLARE it.⠀
⠀
#CannabisinCanada #CannabisauCanada #CannabisAct #LegalizationinCanada #WeedTheNorth
